The '''Bacan myzomela''' ('''''Myzomela batjanensis''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Meliphagidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Indonesia]] where it occurs on the [[Bacan Islands]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s, subtropical or tropical mangrove forests, and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s.

